13/11/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Fourteen people suspected of car thefts have been arrested in a joint operation by Serbian and Montenegrin police services, Serbian Interior Minister Ivica Dacic announced on Thursday (November 12th). 
Six of the suspects were detained in Serbia while the others were apprehended in Montenegro. 
All are alleged members of an organised crime group that stole cars in Serbia to sell in Montenegro. 
Police are searching for two more suspects. 
(Beta, Tanjug, B92 - 12/11/09)
